author: Stefanie Loh
title: WSU Cougars morning links: The day after the upset win vs. Oregon
text:
EUGENE, Ore. — Did you get any sleep after that exhilarating finish, Coug fans?
Here's what it looked like in the @wsucougfb locker room tonight! #GoCougs pic.twitter.com/Wt7ArI3wZm 
— WSU Cougars (@WSUCougars) October 11, 2015 
So proud of these boys right now for grinding it out tonite…
Nothing given, only earned!
 #Work4it #GoCougs ! pic.twitter.com/7cn2ReZzmT 
— Roy Manning (@CoachRoyM) October 11, 2015 

Here’s a look at what the media is saying the morning after Washington State’s 45-38 2OT win over Oregon at Autzen Stadium.
Crimson and Gray win the day this time in Eugene! #Pac12FB pic.twitter.com/AeJh8HKlYR 
Most Read Stories Time for Seahawks to accept that Marshawn Lynch may go from Beast Mode to Decreased Mode Ore. gunman killed instructor who had corrected him days earlier Luke Falk, WSU upset Oregon in double overtime Why Mariners’ firing of Lloyd McClendon was inevitable, who might be next Thousands without power as rain and wind topple trees Unlimited Digital Access. $1 for 4 weeks. — Pac-12 Conference (@pac12) October 11, 2015 

— I had this game recap about how those two overtime periods played out.
— Here, re-live this Jamal Morrow scamper, then read about the emergence of the WSU run game here. 
Jamal Morrow is not going down easy. Here we go! #GoCougs pic.twitter.com/Rok6sb4Jri 
— WSU Cougar Football (@wsucougfb) October 11, 2015 

— Jacob Thorpe from the Spokesman-Review gives you his take on the Cougs’ win , and says the Cougs’ ground game was more effective than Oregon’s passing attack. 
— QB Luke Falk gets an ESPN.com Pac-12 helmet sticker for putting up what Kevin Gemmell called “vintage Air Raid numbers” in WSU’s win.
— Brian Floyd from CougCenter.com says WSU did something special at Oregon. 
— Ken Goe from The Oregonian says WSU’s win was a turning point of sorts for the Ducks. And not in a good way.
— Andrew Greif chronicles how the Ducks fell to the Cougars the season after their appearance in the national championship game.
— The Register-Guard’s Chris Hansen says the Cougars kept battling throughout the game. 
— Oregon offensive coordinator Scott Frost says “we had them where we wanted them.” 
— SI.com also thinks Oregon’s future is in jeopardy after the loss to WSU .
–ESPN.com’s Chantel Jennings calls WSU’s win over Oregon “anti-Couging .” Maybe that should be a thing.
— Everyone loved the way WSU’s athletic department trolled the Lewis & Clark Pioneer uniform-clad Ducks after the Cougs’ big win :
#GoCougs pic.twitter.com/X4txXBLoqd 
— WSU Cougars (@WSUCougars) October 11, 2015 

 
Stefanie Loh
